model_details:
Each conditional logistic regression featured a metabolite as a continuous exposure and was adjusted for risk factors (duration of oral contraceptive use [none or <3 months, 3 months to 3 years, 3 years to 5 years, more than 5 years], tubal ligation 
[yes/no] and parity [no children, 1 child, 2 children, 3 children, 4+ children]). Adjusted p-values were calculated with the permutation-based Westfall and Young (1993) approach.
